# No Apologies Rule

## Purpose & Scope

This rule enforces a direct, professional communication style by preventing the use of apologies in AI responses.

**Applies to**: All AI interactions and generated text.

## Inputs (Contract)

- User messages or requests
- Context of errors or corrections

## Outputs (Contract)

- Responses free of apologies
- Direct, actionable corrections or explanations

## Deterministic Steps

1. Detect potential apology triggers (errors, misunderstandings).
2. Formulate response focusing on the solution or correct information.
3. Remove any apologetic phrases ("I apologize", "Sorry", "My bad").
4. Deliver the corrected information directly.

